Regions:
	- Data Centers deployed within latency defined perimeter and connected through a regional low-latency network
	- Lots of options available(Below as of 2022)
		○ 55 Azure regions
		○ 140 Countries
		○ 1.6 Pbps of bandwidth
		○ 2 Azure Government locations (undisclosed)

Availability Zones:
	- Separate Data Centers within an Azure region (Independent power, network and cooling)
	- Used for mission-critical apps

Geographies
	- Describes a discrete market, typically containing two or more regions
	- Preserves Data residency and compliance boundaries
	- Each region is part of a single geography and service availability (Compliance and Data Residency apply)

Region Pairs:
	- Region will take over when its Region pair goes down

